In a shallow bowl, sprinkle bread with water until soaked, then squeeze dry. In blender, on low speed, blend bread, garlic, egg, egg yolk, salt and pepper, scraping down sides as necessary, until smooth. With motor running on high speed, through hole in top, pour in oil in a very thin stream until incorporated and sauce is thick. On low speed, add lemon juice. Thin with cold water as necessary for desired consistency. Make ahead: Cover and refrigerate for up to 1 week.